<package name="python-configobj" project="openSUSE:Factory">
  <title>ConfigObj is a simple but powerful config file reader and writer</title>
  <description>ConfigObj is a simple but powerful config file reader and writer: an ini file
round tripper. Its main feature is that it is very easy to use, with a
straightforward programmer's interface and a simple syntax for config files.

It has lots of other features though :
* Nested sections (subsections), to any level
* List values
* Multiple line values
* String interpolation (substitution)
* Integrated with a powerful validation system
  including automatic type checking/conversion, repeated sections,
  and allowing default values
* All comments in the file are preserved
* The order of keys/sections is preserved
* No external dependencies
* Full Unicode support
* A powerful unrepr mode for storing basic datatypes</description>
  <devel project="devel:languages:python" package="python-configobj"/>
</package>
